{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id1241ddc6-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777","identifier":"/us/usc/t44/s2905"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2905"},"text":"§ 2905.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Establishment of standards for selective retention of records; security measures","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id1241ddc7-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777","identifier":"/us/usc/t44/s2905/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Archivist shall establish standards for the selective retention of records of continuing value, and assist Federal agencies in applying the standards to records in their custody. The Archivist shall notify the head of a Federal agency of any actual, impending, or threatened unlawful removal, defacing, alteration, or destruction of records in the custody of the agency that shall come to the Archivist’s attention, and assist the head of the agency in initiating action through the Attorney General for the recovery of records unlawfully removed and for other redress provided by law. In any case in which the head of the agency does not initiate an action for such recovery or other redress within a reasonable period of time after being notified of any such unlawful action, the Archivist shall request the Attorney General to initiate such an action, and shall notify the Congress when such a request has been made.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id1241ddc8-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777","identifier":"/us/usc/t44/s2905/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Archivist shall assist the Administrator for the Office of Information and Regulatory Affairs in conducting studies and developing standards relating to record retention requirements imposed on the public and on State and local governments by Federal agencies.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id1241ddc9-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/620"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–620","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1968-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1968","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/82/1296"},"text":"82 Stat. 1296","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/511/s2/c/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–511, § 2(c)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-11"},"text":"Dec. 11, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2825"},"text":"94 Stat. 2825","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/497/tI/s107/b/15/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–497, title I, § 107(b)(15)(B)","children":[],"tail":", title II, § 203(a), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-10-19"},"text":"Oct. 19, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/2288"},"text":"98 Stat. 2288","children":[],"tail":", 2294; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/187/s8/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–187, § 8(8)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-11-26"},"text":"Nov. 26, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/2012"},"text":"128 Stat. 2012","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id1241ddca-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id1241ddcb-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on 44 U.S. Code, 1964 ed., § 395(b) (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-06-30/ch288"},"text":"June 30, 1949, ch. 288","children":[],"tail":", title V, § 505(b), as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-09-05/ch849/s6/d"},"text":"Sept. 5, 1950, ch. 849, § 6(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/583"},"text":"64 Stat. 583","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id1241ddcc-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id1241ddcd-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2014—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/187"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–187","children":[],"tail":" substituted “The Archivist shall notify” for “He shall notify” and “the Archivist’s attention” for “his attention”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/497/s107/b/15/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–497, § 107(b)(15)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Archivist” for “Administrator of General Services”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/497/s203/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–497, § 203(a)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “In any case in which the head of the agency does not initiate an action for such recovery or other redress within a reasonable period of time after being notified of any such unlawful action, the Archivist shall request the Attorney General to initiate such an action, and shall notify the Congress when such a request has been made.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"h